CSS Selectors :

Types of CSS Selectors:
1. CSS Simple Selectors: Used for finding the elements based on simple attributes (id and class)
Types of CSS Simple selectors
a. CSS element selectors: tagname
b. CSS id Selector: #   ----------- for ex: #ID_Attribute_value
c. CSS class Selector: (.)
d. CSS Universal Selector: *



2. CSS Pseudo-class selectors: Used for finding the elements based on element locations/positions/indexes

a. Conditions:
and---------------------------------------- tagName[Attribute='AttributeValue'][Attribute='AttributeValue']
or----------------------------------------- tagNAme,tagName[Attribute='AttributeValue'],[Attribute='AttributeValue']
not (to basically exclude the elements)---- tagNAme.tagName:not([Attribute='AttributeValue'])

b. Pseudo Classes (based on the index): Refer: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dwB9jkFaiuU&list=PLacgMXFs7kl8E5xl-nu_7ZjHN0O4oiFcl&index=5
Without using the tagNames:                    Using the tagNames:
first-child.                                   first-of-type.
last-child.									   last-of-type.
nth-child.									   nth-of-tpe.



3. CSS Combinator selectors: Used defining the relationship between elements in the HTML web page.
Types of Combinator selector
a. Descendant selector-------------------- .Attribute<space>Child_Attribute
b. Child selector------------------------- .Attribute>tagName>Child_Attribute>
c. Adjacent (very next) sibling selector-- tagName[AtrributeName = 'AttributeValue']+tagName 
d. General sibling selector--------------- tagName[AtrributeName = 'AttributeValue']~tagName



4. CSS Attribute selectors: Used for finding the elements based on attributes & attribute values.
Types of Attribute Selectors:
a. AttributeName-------------------------  [AttributeName] or tagName[AttributeName]
b. AttributeValue------------------------  tagName[AttributeName = 'AttributeValue']
c. AttributeValue-PartialText-WholeWord--  tagName[AttributeName~ = 'AttributeValue'] For ex: input[Placeholder ~= 'Enter']
d. AttributeValue-PartialText-Text-------  tagName[AttributeName* = 'AttributeValue'] For ex: input[Placeholder* = 'Ent']
e. AttributeValue-StartsWith-WholeWord---  tagName[AttributeName| = 'Attribute-Value'] For ex: input[Placeholder| = 'id']    word is: 'enter-id'
f. AttributeValue-StartsWith-Text--------  tagName[AttributeName^ = 'Attribute-Value']
g. AttributeValue-EndsWith-Text----------  tagName[AttributeName$ = 'Attribute-Value']

